        <div id="doc1" class="document-content">
          <h4>🔬 Atomic Structure</h4>
          <p>Atoms are the building blocks of matter. They consist of a nucleus (protons + neutrons) and electrons orbiting. Protons have positive charge, neutrons neutral, electrons negative. Atomic number = number of protons. Mass number = protons+neutrons. Electron shells: 2,8,8... Example: Carbon has 6 protons, 6 neutrons (most common).</p>
          <p><strong>Key models:</strong> Dalton, Thomson, Rutherford, Bohr. Quantum model describes electron clouds.</p>
          <p><em>📝 Tip: Isotopes have same protons but different neutrons.</em></p>
        </div>
