        <div id="doc2" class="document-content">
          <h4>💎 Types of Chemical Bonds</h4>
          <p><strong>Ionic bond:</strong> transfer of electrons (metal + nonmetal) → NaCl. <strong>Covalent bond:</strong> sharing electrons (nonmetal + nonmetal) → H2O. <strong>Metallic bond:</strong> electron sea in metals. Polarity, electronegativity differences determine bond type. Lewis structures help visualize bonding.</p>
          <p>💡 Fun fact: Diamond and graphite both pure carbon, different bonding → different properties!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
