          <p>A mole is like a dozen, but huge! One mole of any substance contains Avogadro's number of particles. Molar mass = grams per mole. Use formula: moles = mass / molar mass. Stoichiometry: balanced equations show mole ratios. Example: 2H₂ + O₂ → 2H₂O. 2 moles H₂ react with 1 mole O₂.</p>
          <p>📌 Practice: 18g water = 1 mole water (H₂O molar mass 18 g/mol).</p>
